1005
01:04:12,885 --> 01:04:13,954
Need a pen?

1006
01:04:19,525 --> 01:04:20,826
CHUCK: So much for that.

1007
01:04:22,628 --> 01:04:24,430
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1008
01:04:25,031 --> 01:04:26,096
Come on!

1009
01:04:26,098 --> 01:04:27,700
- No.
- (GRUNTS)

1010
01:04:45,018 --> 01:04:46,885
We are not going
to the red room!

1011
01:04:46,887 --> 01:04:48,220
No, we are going
to the red room.

1012
01:04:48,222 --> 01:04:49,521
- No, I'm not.
- Yes.

1013
01:04:49,523 --> 01:04:50,691
No. I'm not doing it.

1014
01:04:51,591 --> 01:04:52,892
(MUTTERS)

1015
01:04:52,894 --> 01:04:55,227
WOMAN: (ON PA) <i>Dr. Kaufmann
to telephone, please.</i>

1016
01:04:55,229 --> 01:04:57,229
<i>Dr. Kaufmann.</i>

1017
01:04:57,231 --> 01:05:00,969
CHUCK: I told you about my dream.
I don't want to go.

1018
01:05:02,137 --> 01:05:04,672
So, it isn't actually red.
You're fine.

1019
01:05:08,209 --> 01:05:09,976
It is called
the red room, okay?

1020
01:05:09,978 --> 01:05:11,980
Who said it had to be red?

1021
01:05:12,981 --> 01:05:15,047
Uh-uh. Count me out.

1022
01:05:15,049 --> 01:05:17,051
Okay. Just... stay here.

1023
01:05:19,087 --> 01:05:21,190
Be quick. It'll be fine.

1024
01:05:21,823 --> 01:05:22,925
(GROANS)

1025
01:05:23,658 --> 01:05:25,160
Just don't get caught.

1026
01:05:42,312 --> 01:05:43,780
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

1027
01:05:56,292 --> 01:05:57,659
(DOORKNOB RATTLES)

1028
01:05:59,295 --> 01:06:01,064
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1029
01:06:08,738 --> 01:06:09,704
ORDERLY: George Foreman.

1030
01:06:09,706 --> 01:06:12,274
He's going to be
the world champion in '73.

1031
01:06:12,276 --> 01:06:14,278
Hey, you know
where you're going?

1032
01:06:18,983 --> 01:06:21,252
Oh, God. Oh, God,
oh, God, oh, God.

1033
01:06:23,854 --> 01:06:25,954
ORDERLY: Hey, you there.

1034
01:06:25,956 --> 01:06:27,623
You're not supposed
to be here.

1035
01:06:27,625 --> 01:06:29,027
Hey! Stop!

1036
01:06:37,269 --> 01:06:38,870
(BOTH PANTING)

1037
01:06:39,405 --> 01:06:40,605
The R.E.D. room.

1038
01:06:47,045 --> 01:06:48,113
(SWITCH CLICKS)

1039
01:07:06,332 --> 01:07:09,033
RAMON: Admittance records,
psychological exams,

1040
01:07:09,035 --> 01:07:10,701
what she ate...

1041
01:07:10,703 --> 01:07:12,972
STELLA: This is... everything.

1042
01:07:14,006 --> 01:07:15,808
She was admitted
by her own family.

1043
01:07:17,411 --> 01:07:20,711
Says here
that she was suffering

1044
01:07:20,713 --> 01:07:23,181
from achromasia-albinism.

1045
01:07:23,183 --> 01:07:25,719
They put her in her basement
because she was different.

1046
01:07:30,924 --> 01:07:33,192
Here, her supervising
doctor was...

1047
01:07:34,760 --> 01:07:36,196
Dr. Ephraim Bellows.

1048
01:07:36,963 --> 01:07:38,762
Her own brother?

1049
01:07:38,764 --> 01:07:39,799
(SOFTLY) Yeah.

1050
01:07:43,770 --> 01:07:46,905
Jesus! They tortured her.

1051
01:07:46,907 --> 01:07:48,240
Look, electroshock,

1052
01:07:48,242 --> 01:07:50,809
isolation therapy,

1053
01:07:50,811 --> 01:07:53,148
lateral cerebral
diathermia treatment.

1054
01:07:55,782 --> 01:07:56,951
What about this thing?

1055
01:08:03,124 --> 01:08:04,292
What is this?

1056
01:08:07,396 --> 01:08:09,063
I've seen
one of these before.

1057
01:08:10,232 --> 01:08:11,833
It's a wax cylinder.

1058
01:08:16,472 --> 01:08:19,208
They used them to make
recordings before LPs.

1059
01:08:22,944 --> 01:08:25,880
So, does that mean we're going
to get to hear Sarah?

1060
01:08:27,416 --> 01:08:29,151
(PANTING)

1061
01:08:33,422 --> 01:08:35,489
ORDERLY: He went this way.

1062
01:08:35,491 --> 01:08:36,825
Sound the alarm!

1063
01:08:42,199 --> 01:08:45,166
EPHRAIM: (ON EDIPHONE) <i>You're
going to tell the truth now.</i>

1064
01:08:45,168 --> 01:08:46,903
<i>Aren't you, Sarah?</i>

1065
01:08:52,475 --> 01:08:56,012
SARAH: (WEAKLY)
<i>I didn't hurt the children.</i>

1066
01:08:58,216 --> 01:08:59,816
<i>I didn't.</i>

1067
01:09:02,253 --> 01:09:03,219
<i>Ephraim...</i>

1068
01:09:03,221 --> 01:09:07,423
EPHRAIM:
<i>That isn't the truth, is it?</i>

1069
01:09:07,425 --> 01:09:10,124
SARAH: (TEARFULLY)
<i>I didn't do it.</i>

1070
01:09:10,126 --> 01:09:11,460
<i>I didn't hurt...</i>

1071
01:09:11,462 --> 01:09:13,797
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
- (SARAH SCREAMING)

1072
01:09:14,532 --> 01:09:15,930
(CRACKLING STOPS)

1073
01:09:15,932 --> 01:09:17,533
EPHRAIM:
<i>Tell the truth, Sarah.</i>

1074
01:09:17,535 --> 01:09:19,335
SARAH: (SOBS)
<i>I'm your sister...</i>

1075
01:09:19,337 --> 01:09:21,003
EPHRAIM: <i>You poisoned
those children.</i>

1076
01:09:21,005 --> 01:09:23,107
SARAH: <i>No. No.</i>

1077
01:09:23,874 --> 01:09:25,276
<i>I tried...</i>

1078
01:09:26,177 --> 01:09:28,246
<i>I tried to save them.</i>

1079
01:09:30,281 --> 01:09:33,450
<i>But nobody listened.</i>

1080
01:09:33,452 --> 01:09:38,221
<i>I didn't want them hurt,
but you wouldn't let me out.</i>

1081
01:09:38,223 --> 01:09:39,456
EPHRAIM: <i>Sarah...</i>

1082
01:09:39,458 --> 01:09:41,360
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
- (SARAH SCREAMING)

1083
01:09:43,829 --> 01:09:47,130
- (CRACKLING STOPS)
- EPHRAIM: <i>Tell the truth.</i>

1084
01:09:47,132 --> 01:09:48,501
She doesn't know
what she did.

1085
01:09:49,402 --> 01:09:50,867
SARAH: <i>It was the water.</i>

1086
01:09:50,869 --> 01:09:52,836
EPHRAIM:
<i>We went over this, Sarah.</i>

1087
01:09:52,838 --> 01:09:54,372
SARAH: (SOBS) <i>The water.</i>

1088
01:09:54,374 --> 01:09:57,974
EPHRAIM: <i>There's nothing wrong
with the water.</i>

1089
01:09:57,976 --> 01:09:59,509
<i>That's why you're here.</i>

1090
01:09:59,511 --> 01:10:01,111
SARAH: <i>The mill.</i>

1091
01:10:01,113 --> 01:10:03,947
<i>It was the mercury
from the mill.</i>

1092
01:10:03,949 --> 01:10:05,483
<i>You poisoned the wa...</i>

1093
01:10:05,485 --> 01:10:07,487
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
- (SARAH SCREAMING)

1094
01:10:09,055 --> 01:10:10,056
She didn't do it.

1095
01:10:10,590 --> 01:10:11,790
It was her family.

1096
01:10:15,295 --> 01:10:16,396
EPHRAIM: <i>Sarah,</i>

1097
01:10:17,297 --> 01:10:18,898
<i>are you still here?</i>

1098
01:10:22,536 --> 01:10:24,137
SARAH: (IN EERIE TONE)
<i>I'll tell you.</i>

1099
01:10:25,472 --> 01:10:27,807
<i>I'll tell you
what you want to hear.</i>

1100
01:10:28,542 --> 01:10:30,277
EPHRAIM: <i>And what's that?</i>

1101
01:10:31,078 --> 01:10:33,981
(STATIC CRACKLES)

1102
01:10:35,015 --> 01:10:37,419
(WAX CYLINDER
SPINS MECHANICALLY)

1103
01:10:39,086 --> 01:10:42,357
SARAH: <i>Charlie had a dream
of a red room...</i>

1104
01:10:44,625 --> 01:10:45,924
EPHRAIM: <i>Charlie?</i>

1105
01:10:45,926 --> 01:10:46,992
The R.E.D. room.

1106
01:10:46,994 --> 01:10:48,329
EPHRAIM: <i>Charlie who?</i>

1107
01:10:49,196 --> 01:10:50,197
Chuck.

1108
01:10:51,065 --> 01:10:52,433
SARAH: <i>In his dream,</i>

1109
01:10:53,535 --> 01:10:57,102
<i>a woman with a pale face,</i>

1110
01:10:57,104 --> 01:10:59,372
<i>black eyes,</i>

1111
01:10:59,374 --> 01:11:02,241
<i>and long black hair</i>

1112
01:11:02,243 --> 01:11:06,045
<i>slipped silently
into his room.</i>

1113
01:11:06,047 --> 01:11:09,382
SARAH: (WHISPERS)
<i>She leaned over and whispered,</i>

1114
01:11:09,384 --> 01:11:14,120
<i>"This is an evil place.</i>

1115
01:11:14,122 --> 01:11:17,291
<i>"Run away
while you still can."</i>

1116
01:11:17,293 --> 01:11:18,561
(GASPING)

1117
01:11:21,997 --> 01:11:24,098
(ALARM BLARING)

1118
01:11:24,100 --> 01:11:25,569
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

1119
01:11:30,206 --> 01:11:31,373
(SCREAMS)

1120
01:11:31,375 --> 01:11:32,706
(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

1121
01:11:32,708 --> 01:11:34,074
That's not good.

1122
01:11:34,076 --> 01:11:35,144
Chuck!

1123
01:11:36,312 --> 01:11:38,047
(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

1124
01:11:45,154 --> 01:11:46,222
CHUCK: Help!

1125
01:11:47,357 --> 01:11:48,358
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

1126
01:11:49,292 --> 01:11:50,893
Help! Somebody, help!

1127
01:11:52,129 --> 01:11:54,164
(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

1128
01:12:11,649 --> 01:12:13,317
(MOANING SOFTLY)

1129
01:12:17,088 --> 01:12:19,157
(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

1130
01:12:30,501 --> 01:12:32,303
(PANTING)

1131
01:12:38,142 --> 01:12:40,179
Help! Please, somebody, help.

1132
01:12:57,062 --> 01:12:58,531
(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

1133
01:13:18,384 --> 01:13:19,717
Help. Help!

1134
01:13:19,719 --> 01:13:21,787
Somebody, help!

1135
01:13:21,789 --> 01:13:23,389
- Come on!
- (DOORKNOB RATTLING)

1136
01:13:35,269 --> 01:13:37,137
(GASPING)

1137
01:13:44,646 --> 01:13:46,113
(PANTING)

1138
01:13:51,520 --> 01:13:53,321
(WHIMPERING)

1139
01:13:56,257 --> 01:13:58,192
(CHUCK CONTINUES WHIMPERING)

1140
01:13:59,293 --> 01:14:00,428
(CHUCK WHEEZING)

1141
01:14:13,408 --> 01:14:14,777
(MOANS SOFTLY)

1142
01:14:16,546 --> 01:14:19,145
STELLA: Chuck! Chuck,
where are you?

1143
01:14:19,147 --> 01:14:20,148
RAMON: Chuck!

1144
01:14:21,684 --> 01:14:22,750
Where is he?

1145
01:14:22,752 --> 01:14:24,251
He should be right here.

1146
01:14:24,253 --> 01:14:26,487
Chuck? Chuck?

1147
01:14:26,489 --> 01:14:27,657
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

1148
01:14:28,558 --> 01:14:29,592
STELLA: Chuck.

1149
01:14:42,205 --> 01:14:43,671
NURSE: So,

1150
01:14:43,673 --> 01:14:45,274
where's your
little friend?

1151
01:14:47,510 --> 01:14:50,514
MAN: (ON TV) <i>News coverage of
election night '68 continues.</i>

1152
01:14:50,914 --> 01:14:52,781
(PHONE RINGS)

1153
01:14:52,783 --> 01:14:53,882
Stella?

1154
01:14:53,884 --> 01:14:55,483
STELLA: <i>Dad.</i>

1155
01:14:55,485 --> 01:14:56,720
Are you okay? Where are you?

1156
01:14:58,155 --> 01:14:59,254
<i>Stella?</i>

1157
01:14:59,256 --> 01:15:01,323
(VOICE BREAKING) I'm
afraid I'm gonna die, Dad.

1158
01:15:01,325 --> 01:15:03,458
<i>Aw, sweetie, don't say that.</i>

1159
01:15:03,460 --> 01:15:05,628
Tell me what's wrong.
Tell me what I can do.

1160
01:15:05,630 --> 01:15:07,930
<i>Can't do anything about it.</i>

1161
01:15:07,932 --> 01:15:10,198
<i>I can't do anything about it.</i>

1162
01:15:10,200 --> 01:15:13,169
No, no. You gotta help me
out here, sweetie.

1163
01:15:13,171 --> 01:15:15,705
<i>Tell me where you are.
I will get there right away.</i>

1164
01:15:15,707 --> 01:15:17,773
<i>I don't care what you're going
through, just tell me, please.</i>

1165
01:15:17,775 --> 01:15:19,275
If I go missing...

1166
01:15:19,277 --> 01:15:20,411
<i>Missing?</i>

1167
01:15:21,346 --> 01:15:22,648
If you can't find me...

1168
01:15:23,448 --> 01:15:24,483
Find you where?

1169
01:15:26,685 --> 01:15:27,884
<i>Stella?</i>

1170
01:15:27,886 --> 01:15:29,920
I didn't leave you.

1171
01:15:29,922 --> 01:15:32,221
<i>I would never
do that to you.</i>

1172
01:15:32,223 --> 01:15:33,422
I don't understand

1173
01:15:33,424 --> 01:15:34,690
<i>what you're talking about,
Stella, leave me?</i>

1174
01:15:34,692 --> 01:15:35,892
<i>Why would you leave me?</i>

1175
01:15:35,894 --> 01:15:37,730
Is someone there
with you? Do...

1176
01:15:43,267 --> 01:15:45,437
<i>Please just listen to me,
sweetie.</i>

1177
01:15:46,739 --> 01:15:48,540
It's not your fault, Stella.

1178
01:15:49,475 --> 01:15:51,310
<i>It's not your fault she left.</i>

1179
01:15:52,812 --> 01:15:55,545
Everyone said
it was because of me.

1180
01:15:55,547 --> 01:15:58,716
Oh, no, please, please,
please listen to me.

1181
01:15:58,718 --> 01:16:01,419
<i>It's not your fault she left.</i>

1182
01:16:01,421 --> 01:16:05,625
<i>It was never, ever about you.
It was about her.</i>

1183
01:16:08,395 --> 01:16:11,398
<i>I don't know, somewhere deep
down inside, she just...</i>

1184
01:16:12,499 --> 01:16:14,735
<i>felt trapped or something,
I don't know, I...</i>

1185
01:16:15,970 --> 01:16:16,869
It's complicated.

1186
01:16:16,871 --> 01:16:18,671
I wish I had answers
for you, sweetie,

1187
01:16:18,673 --> 01:16:20,740
<i>but I just don't
and I'm so sorry.</i>

1188
01:16:21,941 --> 01:16:23,276
(SNIFFLES)

1189
01:16:24,277 --> 01:16:26,744
I love you, Dad.
I gotta go.

1190
01:16:26,746 --> 01:16:29,313
It's not your fault, Stella.
Please don't hang up, sweetie.

1191
01:16:29,315 --> 01:16:30,348
I'm sorry, I'm sorry,
I gotta go.

1192
01:16:30,350 --> 01:16:31,251
<i>I'm telling you,
it wasn't your...</i>

1193
01:16:33,788 --> 01:16:36,457
So? Is your dad going to come
pick you up?

1194
01:16:38,926 --> 01:16:41,930
Oh, Stella,
what's going on?

1195
01:16:43,464 --> 01:16:45,599
I need answers from you
right now.

1196
01:16:46,001 --> 01:16:47,901
Understand?

1197
01:16:47,903 --> 01:16:51,371
<i>Richard Nixon is still holding
at 43 and Humphrey 35,</i>

1198
01:16:51,373 --> 01:16:53,707
<i>but, uh, Wallace
has come up one point.</i>

1199
01:16:53,709 --> 01:16:55,375
What about my call?

1200
01:16:55,377 --> 01:16:57,980
Rules don't apply
to draft dodgers.

1201
01:16:59,448 --> 01:17:00,549
You think
I wouldn't find out?

1202
01:17:01,751 --> 01:17:04,752
Ramon Morales.

1203
01:17:04,754 --> 01:17:06,620
You're gonna do your duty
to this country

1204
01:17:06,622 --> 01:17:08,054
one way or the other.

1205
01:17:08,056 --> 01:17:11,291
I can help you if you tell us
about your missing friends.

1206
01:17:11,293 --> 01:17:13,326
Told you everything we know.

1207
01:17:13,328 --> 01:17:14,463
(CHUCKLES) Oh, yeah, right.

1208
01:17:15,363 --> 01:17:17,865
Sarah Bellows' book.

1209
01:17:17,867 --> 01:17:21,971
The stories write themselves
and it all comes alive.

1210
01:17:23,438 --> 01:17:24,974
We can't find any bodies.

1211
01:17:25,808 --> 01:17:27,009
Yeah, I know.

1212
01:17:28,478 --> 01:17:29,645
It's hard to believe.

1213
01:17:30,780 --> 01:17:32,813
We saved Ruth at school.

1214
01:17:32,815 --> 01:17:34,852
I mean, we stopped her
from getting killed.

1215
01:17:36,920 --> 01:17:38,754
Ruth Steinberg?

1216
01:17:38,756 --> 01:17:40,389
That's who
you're talking about?

1217
01:17:41,492 --> 01:17:42,657
You didn't save anyone.

1218
01:17:42,659 --> 01:17:45,729
She's stuck in the nuthouse
for the rest of her life.

1219
01:17:46,897 --> 01:17:49,865
Get out of here, Stella.
You're free to go.

1220
01:17:49,867 --> 01:17:52,669
You're so much better
than this draft dodger.

1221
01:17:53,705 --> 01:17:55,706
Come on,
what would your father say?

1222
01:17:57,474 --> 01:17:58,675
I'm not leaving.

1223
01:18:01,512 --> 01:18:02,944
Since you're not
going to 'Nam,

1224
01:18:02,946 --> 01:18:05,984
maybe a night behind bars will
loosen those lips of yours.

1225
01:18:08,119 --> 01:18:10,787
- Come on, Hobbs.
- (LOCK CLICKS)

1226
01:18:10,789 --> 01:18:12,722
Go home,
dig out that 10 bucks

1227
01:18:12,724 --> 01:18:15,057
you're gonna owe me
when Nixon wins,

1228
01:18:15,059 --> 01:18:16,659
and, uh,
I'll close up here.

1229
01:18:16,661 --> 01:18:17,794
HOBBS: All right,
have a good night.

1230
01:18:17,796 --> 01:18:19,364
Nighty-night, lovebirds.

1231
01:18:20,565 --> 01:18:21,900
I should've told you.

1232
01:18:23,601 --> 01:18:25,002
You must think
I'm a coward, but...

1233
01:18:25,004 --> 01:18:26,739
I would never think that.

1234
01:18:35,381 --> 01:18:38,651
Two months ago they shipped
my brother back from Vietnam

1235
01:18:39,785 --> 01:18:40,954
in pieces.

1236
01:18:41,855 --> 01:18:43,454
I'm so sorry.

1237
01:18:46,859 --> 01:18:49,028
Last week when I got
my draft notice,

1238
01:18:51,697 --> 01:18:52,698
I couldn't.

1239
01:18:53,699 --> 01:18:54,900
They just send you there
to die.

1240
01:18:56,769 --> 01:18:57,904
If the book reads me,

1241
01:18:59,973 --> 01:19:01,741
I'm afraid
what it's going to say.

1242
01:19:11,152 --> 01:19:12,686
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

1243
01:19:28,970 --> 01:19:30,903
TURNER: There you go, boy.

1244
01:19:30,905 --> 01:19:32,372
Yeah, that's good, huh?

1245
01:19:40,715 --> 01:19:43,084
"Me Tie Dough-ty Walker"?

1246
